Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a concave area with wood impressions and perpendicular to it two wide string impressions of 0.36 cm. The top rounded at the sides with finger impressions, parts of a seal impression are preserved showing a j-reed (M27), a nfr and maybe a seated figure.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
